1 structure of DNA

In fact, it is easy to remember the molecular structure of DNA. First, there is a 2-deoxyribose (pentose or ) 1-carbon connects to a base, 5-carbon connects to a phosphate group which connects to the next deoxyribose at 3. A nucleotide contains one base, one deoxyribose and one tri-phosphate. It is important to remember that the 5 end of dna is the 3 carbon side.
